            <div type="glosses">
                <note xml:id="TRAVELGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;Papas leaving home was a moment of sorrow / because he was not to come back to&#x2010;morrow / 
                    but we thought that the whole was a travel and now / he might come back in days&#x201D; (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSI">MS I</title>)&#x2014;</hi>Read as a commentary on real life, 
                    the poem means that <persName corresp="#JJR">John James Ruskin</persName> has departed on a business journey that is not a day&#x02bc;s commute, 
                    such as Papa&#x02bc;s early&#x2010;morning departure for <placeName corresp="#LONDON">London</placeName> at the start of 
                    <ref type="witness" target="harry_and_lucy_vol1_msi.php"><title type="lesson" corresp="#JRHARRYANDLUCY">&#x201C;Harry and Lucy . . . Vol I&#x201D;</title></ref>, 
                    but that is a longer &#x201c;travel&#x201d; through the country, collecting orders for wine from clients. However, the second couplet suggests, 
                    plans have changed, and he may return home in a matter of days instead of weeks. None of the extant letters between <persName corresp="#JJR">John James</persName> and <persName corresp="#MR">Margaret Ruskin</persName> 
                    for <date notBefore="1816" notAfter="1827">1826&#x2013;27</date> suggest an unexpected curtailment of a business trip.
                </p></note>

                <note xml:id="ALSOSOMETHINGUNIQUEGLOSS" resp="#DCH">This is another gloss.</note><!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_contextual" target="filename_glosses.php#ALSOSOMETHINGUNIQUEGLOSS"/>.-->
